> Imagine you have like a test server or like a general server,
  and the application on this server stops working, what will
  by your steps to check, to verify why it dosen't work and how
  to probably fix it: what will you do:

  - so basically, if an application on a server stops working, my approach would
    be to troubleshoot step by step

  - first i would check whether the server itself is up and reachable, for example
    by pinging or trying to access it

  - if the server is up, then i would check if the application services is running or not

  - if it is not running, i would try to restart the service and see if it comes back up

  - next, i would check the application logs and system logs to identify an errors or failure message

  - from my experience, logs usually give the exact root cause

  - then, i would verify if there are any recent changes, like deployments or configuration
    updates, which could have caused the issues

  - i would also check system resources like CPU, memory and disk space, because
    sometimes the application may fail due to resource issues

  - if the issue is related to connectivity, i would check network configurations, ports and
    dependencies like database or external services

  - So basically, my approach is to check server status, application service, logs, resources,
    and dependencies, and then resolve the issue step by step.



